<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870713-0034 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Tops Markets Inc.</HL><DD> 07/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TPPSTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)FOOD andamp; BEVERAGE, HOUSEHOLD GOODS, SUPERMARKETS, TOBACCO (FAB) </IN><TEXT>   Tops Markets Inc. said RFS Buffalo Acquisition Corp. completed its tender offer to acquire the Buffalo, N.Y., supermarket chain for $33.50 a share, or about $196 million, in a leveraged buyout. RFS, formed for the buyout by Riordan Freeman andamp; Spogli, a Los Angeles merchant banking firm, purchased 91.4% of Tops's 5.9 million shares outstanding before the offer expired last Thursday and will buy the remainder under a merger accord. Tops said current management will continue to run the company. For its fiscal first nine months ended March 28, Tops earned $7.9 million, or $1.35 a share, on revenue of $605.3 million. </TEXT></DOC>